---
import AstroshipLayout from "../layouts/AstroshipLayout.astro";
import Container from "../components/container.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<AstroshipLayout
  title="Security Policy - Shout.com"
  description="Shout.com Security Policy. Learn about our security infrastructure, encryption, compliance standards, and how we protect your data."
>
  <section class="py-16">
    <Container>
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Security Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          Last Updated: December 2024
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Quick Navigation -->
      <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-semibold mb-4">Security Topics</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <li><a href="#infrastructure" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Infrastructure Security</a></li>
          <li><a href="#encryption" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Encryption Standards</a></li>
          <li><a href="#access-control" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Access Control</a></li>
          <li><a href="#incident-response" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Incident Response</a></li>
          <li><a href="#compliance" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Compliance</a></li>
          <li><a href="#reporting" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Security Reporting</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-8">
        <!-- Overview Section -->
        <section>
          <div class="flex gap-4 mb-4">
            <Icon name="bx:shield-alt" class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" />
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Security Overview</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                Shout.com places the highest priority on the security and privacy of our customers' data. We employ industry-leading security practices to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Our security approach is comprehensive, spanning infrastructure, application, network, and organizational levels. We operate with a zero-trust security framework and maintain continuous security monitoring.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Infrastructure Section -->
        <section id="infrastructure">
          <div class="flex gap-4 mb-4">
            <Icon name="bx:server" class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" />
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Infrastructure Security</h2>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Data Centers</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                Our primary and standby data centers are located in the United Kingdom and meet the highest security standards. All facilities include:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>ISO 27001:2013 certification</li>
                <li>24/7 physical security with access controls</li>
                <li>CCTV surveillance and monitoring</li>
                <li>Backup generators and cooling systems</li>
                <li>Fire suppression systems</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Geographic Redundancy</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                We maintain a hot-standby server in a different data center supplied by a different provider. This ensures:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>Automatic failover in case of data center failure</li>
                <li>Protection against fire, flood, and provider outages</li>
                <li>Near-zero downtime for business continuity</li>
                <li>Real-time database synchronization</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Network Security</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                <li>Next-Generation (NG) firewalls with Deep Packet Inspection</li>
                <li>Enterprise-grade malware/security suites</li>
                <li>Web Application Firewall (WAF) via Cloudflare</li>
                <li>DDoS protection</li>
                <li>Intrusion Detection and Prevention Systems (IDS/IPS)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Encryption Section -->
        <section id="encryption">
          <div class="flex gap-4 mb-4">
            <Icon name="bx:lock-open" class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" />
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Encryption Standards</h2>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Encryption in Transit</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                All data transmitted between your devices and our servers is encrypted using:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>TLS 1.2 or higher (minimum)</li>
                <li>Strong cipher suites (AES 128 or higher)</li>
                <li>Perfect Forward Secrecy (PFS)</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Encryption at Rest</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                All sensitive data stored on our servers is encrypted using:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>AES 128-bit encryption or higher</li>
                <li>BitLocker encryption for staff devices</li>
                <li>Encrypted backups with separate encryption keys</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Key Management</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Encryption keys are managed securely with restricted access and regular rotation schedules in compliance with industry standards.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Access Control Section -->
        <section id="access-control">
          <div class="flex gap-4 mb-4">
            <Icon name="bx:key" class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" />
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Access Control & Authentication</h2>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Zero-Trust Framework</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                We implement a zero-trust security model that requires:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>Authentication and validation for all users and devices</li>
                <li>Continuous verification of security posture</li>
                <li>Principle of least privilege</li>
                <li>Multiple layers of verification</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Multi-Factor Authentication</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>FIDO hardware security keys for critical services</li>
                <li>Biometric authentication (Windows Hello)</li>
                <li>Time-based One-Time Password (TOTP) 2FA</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Staff Security</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                <li>Single Sign-On (SSO) with 2FA protection</li>
                <li>Device health monitoring via Microsoft Intune</li>
                <li>Conditional access policies</li>
                <li>Regular security awareness training</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Incident Response Section -->
        <section id="incident-response">
          <div class="flex gap-4 mb-4">
            <Icon name="bx:error" class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" />
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Incident Response</h2>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Detection & Monitoring</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                We maintain continuous security monitoring including:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>Real-time log analysis and correlation</li>
                <li>Intrusion detection systems</li>
                <li>Vulnerability scanning</li>
                <li>Security information and event management (SIEM)</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Response Procedures</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                In the event of a security incident, we:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>Immediately investigate and contain the incident</li>
                <li>Notify affected customers without undue delay</li>
                <li>Document findings and remediation steps</li>
                <li>Implement preventive measures</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Patch Management</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                Security patches and updates are applied weekly either automatically or after thorough testing. We use patch management software to verify all systems are updated.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Compliance Section -->
        <section id="compliance">
          <div class="flex gap-4 mb-4">
            <Icon name="bx:check-double" class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" />
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Compliance Standards</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                Our security practices comply with international standards and regulations:
              </p>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Data Protection Regulations</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation)</li>
                <li>UK-GDPR</li>
                <li>CCPA (California Consumer Privacy Act)</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Security Standards</h3>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>ISO 27001:2013 (Information Security Management)</li>
                <li>SOC 2 Type I/II (Service Organization Control)</li>
                <li>OWASP Top 10 vulnerability protection</li>
              </ul>

              <p class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4 text-gray-700">
                <strong>[LEGAL REVIEW REQUIRED]</strong> - Verify all compliance claims are current and accurately reflect your certification status.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Reporting Section -->
        <section id="reporting">
          <div class="flex gap-4 mb-4">
            <Icon name="bx:message-detail" class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" />
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Security Reporting</h2>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Vulnerability Disclosure</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                If you discover a security vulnerability, please responsibly disclose it to us at:
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                <a href="mailto:security@shout.com" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline font-semibold">security@shout.com</a>
              </p>

              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                Please do not publicly disclose the vulnerability before we have had the opportunity to address it. We will:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mb-6">
                <li>Acknowledge receipt within 48 hours</li>
                <li>Investigate and address the issue</li>
                <li>Provide updates on remediation efforts</li>
                <li>Credit you in security advisories (if desired)</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Security Audits</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                We conduct regular independent security audits and penetration tests to ensure our systems remain secure. We work with third-party security firms to validate our security measures.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Contact Section -->
        <section class="mt-12 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Security Questions?</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            If you have questions about our security practices or wish to report a security concern, please contact us.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
            <a href="mailto:security@shout.com" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 transition">
              <Icon name="bx:envelope" class="w-5 h-5" />
              Report Security Issue
            </a>
            <a href="/contact/" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 border border-blue-600 text-blue-600 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-50 transition">
              <Icon name="bx:message-dots" class="w-5 h-5" />
              Contact Us
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</AstroshipLayout>
